The Governor of Kaduna State, Mallam Nasir El-Rufai has tested positive for coronavirus. El-Rufai made the announcement in a statement he personally signed and released to the media on Saturday. The governor is currently in self-isolation in line with the guidelines of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control. He said that his deputy would continue to handle efforts of the state government in combating the spread of the virus. Other top government officials, including governors are still awaiting their test results, having come in contact with those that had tested positive. Details later.. 